<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100897403430164></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100897403430164><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=100897403430164>RE: Two hand or 1 hand weapons for shaman</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=100897403430164#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85776><span id=Sage>Cannis of the Seven Seas</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>382 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Dec 21st 5:33 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I personally would never just train one melee skill with all the new weapons out there it is best to leave yourself options on what you can use. The problem with 2hb is that if you miss your long delay will keep your damage output along the same lines as a fast high damage 1hb or piercer. Plus you wont get the AC bonus that comes along with using a shield in the offhand. I would prefer if I am in melee solo to have the higher AC and faster high damage weapon. In group that would be the time to pull out the 2hb and go to town.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Dec 21 18:02:54 2001</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Cannis 47 Ranger<br>Razer 42st Sk<br>Jeetkundo 20th Monk<br>Mikaraz 26th Warrior<br>Taranthian 30th Necro</td></tr>
